(3.2 For the Uninitiated) show newline
(-----------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    \(about\)      ; What is this place?) show newline
(    \(huh?\)       ; Same question, different inflection) show newline
(    \(what?\)      ; Still the same) show newline
(    \(describe\)   ; For the formal) show newline
() show newline
(The answer morphs with the weave. Standing alone, it suggests) show newline
(enrollment. With peers, it lists them. The description reflects the) show newline
(current state--not a static brochure but a living mirror of the) show newline
(constellation.) show newline
() show newline
(Cyberspace is a system for storing and sharing digital documents, code,) show newline
(and data without relying on any company, government, or central) show newline
(authority. Instead of trusting a corporation to keep your files safe,) show newline
(you and people you trust keep copies that are cryptographically) show newline
(signed--meaning anyone can verify who created something and that it) show newline
(hasn't been tampered with. If one computer goes offline, the others) show newline
(still have everything. Your data belongs to you, verified by math,) show newline
(preserved by the people you choose.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
