(5.2 Why Ragas?) show newline
(--------------) show newline
() show newline
(Indian classical music assigns ragas to specific times of day. A morning) show newline
(raga played at midnight is wrong--not because of rules, but because it) show newline
(doesn't fit. The music knows when it should be heard.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(5.3 Why a Breathing Lambda?) show newline
(---------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(The lambda isn't just a logo--it's the fundamental unit. What Scheme) show newline
(computes, what the weave is made of. Every function, every object, every) show newline
(sealed thing in the vault is lambdas all the way down.) show newline
() show newline
(The color morphing isn't decoration--it's the weave breathing. Lambdas) show newline
(are being gathered, tested, frozen into vaults across time zones. The) show newline
(color you see is the pulse of that activity. Dawn gold as the eastern) show newline
(hemisphere wakes and contributes. Phosphor green at peak hours. Cyan in) show newline
(the quiet night when the squirrels rest.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
